abstract: Pauline Cafferkey, nurse who has already twice recovered from Ebola, is being treated by infectious disease team at Royal Free Hospital for 'late complications' from her last run-in with virus.

headline.print_headline: Europe; Britain: Setback for Nurse With Ebola
headline.main: Britain: Setback for Nurse With Ebola

snippet: The Royal Free Hospital in London has admitted a Scottish nurse who has already recovered from Ebola twice before for another “late complication.”
lead_paragraph: The Royal Free Hospital in London has admitted a Scottish nurse who has already recovered from Ebola twice before for another “late complication.”
